    "privileged_info_summary": "The brightness_contrast@1 task tests agent ability to improve underexposed images using GIMP's brightness and contrast adjustment tools. The input image is sourced from Unsplash (photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4 or fallback photo-1518837695005-2083093ee35b), both real 800x533 JPEG images. If downloads fail, a synthetic dark image is created using ImageMagick. The verifier uses LAB color space analysis (via scikit-image) to measure brightness (5-50 unit improvement required) and contrast (≥3 std dev increase) changes, with RGB fallback if scikit-image unavailable. Success requires 3/4 criteria: brightness improved, contrast enhanced, <2% pixel clipping, and meaningful change detected. Task has 90-second timeout, 10-step limit, and sparse rewards. Output file is enhanced_landscape.jpg saved to /home/ga/Desktop/.",
